RACE.FOOTNOTES: AUNTIE BEV broke midpack, sent and cleared rivals in the backstretch, continued clear on the turn, lugged out five to six paths heading into the stretch, rider let her keep her momentum and kept to task to the wire to prove best. ABBEY OOPS chased pace three wide on the backstretch, continued three to four wide on the turn, in range in upper stretch and gave way in the final sixteenth. AM YISRAEL CHAI stalked pace along the inside on the backstretch, continued along the rail on the turn and came up empty when roused in the lane. PLEASE NOTE, RACE WAS HAND TIMED
